{"key":"post-14883136","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14883136</id>\n<content>Generally, when bags tear open is on the cool-down cycle.&amp;nbsp; Try to let the pressure fall from 15 psi as slowly as you can.&amp;nbsp; In fact, you can let it drop to 12, then turn the stove back on for a minute or so, then let it drop to 10 psi and repeat, etc.&amp;nbsp; This will allow your bags more time to equalize the pressure.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14883239</next>\n<prev>14882853</prev>\n<first>14880540</first>\n<last>27394670</last>\n<when>1312690525</when>\n<utime>08/07/11 07:15 AM</utime>\n</post>"}